Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.49,0:00:11.20,Show_Title,Screen,0,0,0,,{\c&H0200E9&\3c&H000000&}JUJUTSU KAISEN
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.46,0:00:38.63,Show_Title,Screen,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,650)\c&H2E2C2C&}JUJUTSU KAISEN\N{\fs12\c&HF3F3F3&\bord0\alpha&HFF&\t(237,736,1 \alpha&H00&)}The Culling Game Part 1
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.88,0:01:59.89,Ep_Title,,0,0,0,,Episode 49\N{\fs30}One More Time
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.42,0:02:01.51,Main,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,I'm sorry,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.34,0:02:04.45,Main,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,Itadori-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.09,0:02:09.52,Main,Sukuna,0,0,0,,Tsk.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.09,0:02:43.17,Italics,Choso,0,0,0,,He's fast!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.17,0:02:45.60,Italics,Choso,0,0,0,,I can't figure out the \Ntrick to his technique!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.60,0:02:47.98,Italics,Choso,0,0,0,,With him overwhelming \Nme this badly already,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.98,0:02:50.23,Italics,Choso,0,0,0,,he's not likely to reveal his hand, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.23,0:02:53.06,Italics,Choso,0,0,0,,I have no chance to use Convergence!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.37,0:02:56.77,Italics,Choso,0,0,0,,None of my external Blood \NManipulation is usable here!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.58,0:03:07.96,Main,Naoya,0,0,0,,You're persistent.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.96,0:03:09.87,Main,Naoya,0,0,0,,Seriously, what are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.71,0:03:11.66,Main,Choso,0,0,0,,An older brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.07,0:03:14.16,Main,Choso,0,0,0,,To nine other siblings.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.79,0:03:17.55,Italics,Choso,0,0,0,,{\an8}Flowing Red Scale - Stack!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.17,0:03:17.55,Sign_Basic,Screen,0,0,0,,{\pos(320,315)\fs16\fnTimes New Roman\b1\bord0\shad0\c&HDCE2E8&}Flowing Red Scale - Stack
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.55,0:03:20.04,Main,Naoya,0,0,0,,That ain't an answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.04,0:03:22.26,Main,Naoya,0,0,0,,I was asking about
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.26,0:03:24.80,Main,Naoya,0,0,0,,your toughness and that technique...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.82,0:03:44.82,Italics,Naoya,0,0,0,,He's starting to match me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.39,0:03:54.15,Italics,Naoya,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.15,0:03:56.15,Italics,Naoya,0,0,0,,Flowing Red Scale, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.15,0:03:58.96,Italics,Naoya,0,0,0,,He's focusing that power \Non his external eye muscles
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.96,0:04:01.17,Italics,Naoya,0,0,0,,to improve his kinetic vision.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.03,0:04:03.33,Main,Naoya,0,0,0,,Too bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.33,0:04:06.38,Main,Naoya,0,0,0,,I'm setting motions on the \Nassumption of a counter.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.50,0:04:10.51,Main,Naoya,0,0,0,,You're persistent, so I \Nwent ahead and used it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.51,0:04:11.39,Main,Naoya,0,0,0,,My weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.79,0:04:13.12,Main,Naoya,0,0,0,,You've got Blood Manipulation,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.12,0:04:15.05,Main,Naoya,0,0,0,,so staunching blood flow\Nshould be your forte.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.05,0:04:17.42,Main,Naoya,0,0,0,,Let's find out how well you fare against me
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.42,0:04:20.07,Main,Naoya,0,0,0,,while distracted with \Nstaunching your bleeding.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.07,0:04:21.69,Main,Choso,0,0,0,,You came well prepared.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.69,0:04:23.25,Main,Naoya,0,0,0,,Keep it a secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.25,0:04:25.33,Main,Naoya,0,0,0,,Honestly, I think it's lame.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.33,0:04:27.63,Main,Naoya,0,0,0,,A sorcerer walking around with a weapon?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.63,0:04:30.39,Main,Naoya,0,0,0,,Feels strange if you can't win without it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.39,0:04:33.70,Main,Naoya,0,0,0,,A surprising number of \Npeople share this idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.70,0:04:37.02,Main,Naoya,0,0,0,,My own older brothers are pathetic, \Ncarrying them around.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.02,0:04:40.71,Main,Naoya,0,0,0,,Yet they think they have any right \Nto complain about Toji-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.71,0:04:43.67,Main,Choso,0,0,0,,You hate them, don't you? Your brothers?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.67,0:04:45.10,Main,Naoya,0,0,0,,I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.10,0:04:48.76,Main,Naoya,0,0,0,,Older brothers who are less competent \Nthan a younger brother serve no purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.76,0:04:51.13,Main,Naoya,0,0,0,,They deserve to be hung.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.13,0:04:53.55,Main,Choso,0,0,0,,You might be who you are now
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.55,0:04:56.27,Main,Choso,0,0,0,,thanks to those older brothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.63,0:04:57.50,Main,Naoya,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.50,0:05:01.24,Main,Naoya,0,0,0,,Did you just say something super disgusting?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.24,0:05:03.24,Main,Naoya,0,0,0,,I'm grossed out.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.06,0:05:06.41,Main,Choso,0,0,0,,Competent or not, older brothers
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.41,0:05:08.79,Main,Choso,0,0,0,,serve as an example to their younger brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.24,0:05:11.16,Main,Choso,0,0,0,,If I go down the wrong path,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.16,0:05:13.65,Main,Choso,0,0,0,,then my little brothers \Ncan just avoid that path.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.95,0:05:16.22,Main,Choso,0,0,0,,And if I go down the proper path,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.22,0:05:18.60,Main,Choso,0,0,0,,then my little brothers can follow after me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.01,0:05:20.61,Main,Choso,0,0,0,,What would you do
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.61,0:05:23.69,Main,Choso,0,0,0,,if you were strong because your \Nolder brothers proved weak?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.19,0:05:26.42,Main,Choso,0,0,0,,You asked me why I'm so tough?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.88,0:05:28.46,Main,Choso,0,0,0,,I'll tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.46,0:05:30.32,Main,Choso,0,0,0,,I never had an example.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.32,0:05:32.62,Main,Choso,0,0,0,,I had to make many, many, many mistakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.62,0:05:36.76,Main,Choso,0,0,0,,Yet I always had to keep \Nwalking in front of my brothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.76,0:05:39.03,Main,Choso,0,0,0,,That's why I'm strong!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.19,0:05:44.96,Italics,Naoya,0,0,0,,What's he on about?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.96,0:05:47.20,Italics,Naoya,0,0,0,,How's he still alive after bleeding so much?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.96,0:05:58.79,Narration,Narrator,0,0,0,,The Death Paintings are \Na mix of curse and human.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.79,0:06:03.06,Narration,Narrator,0,0,0,,They possess the unique ability to \Nconvert cursed energy into blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.06,0:06:08.03,Narration,Narrator,0,0,0,,Until their cursed energy dries up, \Nthey cannot die from blood loss.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.22,0:06:35.65,Italics,Naoya,0,0,0,,My legs are heavy?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.65,0:06:39.17,Italics,Naoya,0,0,0,,Did he harden the blood that \Nseeped into the fabric?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.99,0:06:41.54,Main,Choso,0,0,0,,You get it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.66,0:06:44.17,Main,Choso,0,0,0,,It's checkmate.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.50,0:06:52.41,Main,Naoya,0,0,0,,I'm not sure about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.53,0:06:56.16,Italics,Naoya,0,0,0,,My technique traces the motions
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.16,0:06:58.72,Italics,Naoya,0,0,0,,set ahead of time at 24 fps.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.72,0:07:01.77,Italics,Naoya,0,0,0,,I can still move without issue \Nunder this minor a hindrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.77,0:07:04.67,Italics,Naoya,0,0,0,,Let's try it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.00,0:07:10.90,Italics,Naoya,0,0,0,,Why isn't he firing at me?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.90,0:07:12.88,Narration,Narrator,0,0,0,,{\an8}This was Choso's original,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.88,0:07:17.67,Narration,Narrator,0,0,0,,{\an8}developed after grappling with \Nhis technique for 150 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.62,0:07:17.66,Sign_Basic,Screen,0,0,0,,{\pos(320,315)\fs16\fnTimes New Roman\b1\bord0\shad0\c&HDCE2E8&}Supernova
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.81,0:07:47.50,Main,Choso,0,0,0,,Sorry, but I can't understand how \Nyou could never love your brothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.21,0:08:12.22,Main,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,That looks painful,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.36,0:08:14.47,Main,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,Naoya-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.68,0:08:20.45,Main,Naoya,0,0,0,,Don't look down on me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.43,0:08:28.23,Italics,Naoya,0,0,0,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.23,0:08:29.17,Italics,Naoya,0,0,0,,Poison?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.52,0:08:32.69,Italics,Naoya,0,0,0,,Blood Manipulation shouldn't be capable of—
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.69,0:08:35.67,Italics,Naoya,0,0,0,,No! It's not a product of his technique!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.67,0:08:39.46,Italics,Naoya,0,0,0,,He had that much blood \Nbecause he's not human!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.46,0:08:41.10,Italics,Naoya,0,0,0,,An incarnation?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.10,0:08:44.69,Italics,Naoya,0,0,0,,His inhuman blood got into my \Nbody and is being rejected!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.69,0:08:46.46,Main,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,Shall I heal you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.62,0:08:51.24,Main,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,My reverse cursed technique \Ncan heal people, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.63,0:08:53.04,Main,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,In return,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.63,0:08:56.90,Main,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,could you please report Itadori-kun's death
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.90,0:08:58.99,Main,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,to the top brass, as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.77,0:09:02.75,Flashback,Yuji's Grandfather,0,0,0,,Jin!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.97,0:09:10.93,Flashback,Jin,0,0,0,,What is it, Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.53,0:09:14.18,Flashback,Jin,0,0,0,,If you want to talk about \Nher, I'm going home.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.94,0:09:16.04,Flashback,Yuji's Grandfather,0,0,0,,Jin!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.43,0:09:19.47,Flashback,Yuji's Grandfather,0,0,0,,You're free to live your \Nlife however you please.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.23,0:09:23.64,Flashback,Yuji's Grandfather,0,0,0,,But you have to stay away from that woman!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.64,0:09:24.54,Flashback,Yuji's Grandfather,0,0,0,,You'll die!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.84,0:09:29.34,Flashback,Jin,0,0,0,,Please stop saying such mean \Nthings in front of Yuji.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.34,0:09:32.61,Flashback,Jin,0,0,0,,You'd be surprised at how \Nmuch a baby can remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.05,0:09:35.80,Flashback,Yuji's Grandfather,0,0,0,,I know that you've wanted a child,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.80,0:09:39.49,Flashback,Yuji's Grandfather,0,0,0,,and I know you were never \Nable to do that with Kaori.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.09,0:09:42.29,Flashback,Yuji's Grandfather,0,0,0,,But Kaori died—
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.68,0:09:45.50,Flashback,Kaori,0,0,0,,Father, what are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.73,0:10:01.88,Main,Yuji,0,0,0,,Huh? I'm...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.00,0:10:23.33,Main,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,Th-Thank goodness!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.89,0:10:26.08,Main,Yuji,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.49,0:10:32.47,Main,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,Around September, I think?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.08,0:10:35.60,Main,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,Gojo-sensei went out of his way to see me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.19,0:10:38.61,Main,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,He asked me to take care of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.37,0:10:43.24,Main,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,So I had no choice but to put on that act.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.56,0:10:44.64,Main,Yuji,0,0,0,,Act?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.53,0:10:48.50,Flashback,Gojo,0,0,0,,I've got a bit of a bad feeling,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.50,0:10:50.27,Flashback,Gojo,0,0,0,,so if anything happens to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.27,0:10:53.58,Flashback,Gojo,0,0,0,,I want you to take care of the \Nfirst- and second-years, Yuta.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.58,0:10:55.78,Flashback,Gojo,0,0,0,,Hakari? Well, he'll be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.46,0:10:57.81,Flashback,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,If anything happens?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.21,0:11:00.26,Flashback,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,Troubles with women?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.05,0:11:04.16,Flashback,Gojo,0,0,0,,You've learned to joke \Naround, haven't you, Yuta?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.16,0:11:08.50,Flashback,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,No, I just can't imagine anything \Nhappening to you, Gojo-sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.76,0:11:12.21,Flashback,Gojo,0,0,0,,Take special care of Yuji Itadori.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.21,0:11:14.02,Flashback,Gojo,0,0,0,,He's been sentenced to
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.02,0:11:16.50,Flashback,Gojo,0,0,0,,secret execution, like you were.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.50,0:11:19.24,Flashback,Gojo,0,0,0,,It'd be a big help if you looked out for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.48,0:11:21.51,Flashback,Gojo,0,0,0,,Oh, how's Miguel?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.51,0:11:23.81,Flashback,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,He said he didn't want to see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.81,0:11:24.93,Flashback,Gojo,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.83,0:11:28.58,Main,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,I decided that putting on \Nthis act was the best option
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.58,0:11:31.17,Main,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,to prevent someone else from \Nbeing sent to execute you
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.17,0:11:33.90,Main,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,and having information about you cut off.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.90,0:11:36.16,Main,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,Well, they're not idiots, either,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.16,0:11:40.68,Main,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,so before they would approve \Nme as the executioner,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.68,0:11:43.85,Main,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,HQ made me forge a pact to kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.85,0:11:45.62,Main,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,So I did have to kill you for a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.62,0:11:46.99,Main,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,I'm real sorry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.84,0:11:53.27,Main,Yuji,0,0,0,,Wait, then how am I alive?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.16,0:11:55.96,Main,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,The reverse cursed technique.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.25,0:11:59.61,Main,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,I used my reverse cursed technique
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.61,0:12:02.36,Main,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,the moment your heart stopped \Nto immediately heal you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.11,0:12:06.80,Main,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,I figured it would work, \Ngiven what I heard about you before.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.32,0:12:12.06,Main,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,There are few people who know I'm \Ncapable of outputting positive energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.49,0:12:13.62,Main,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.85,0:12:17.23,Main,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,This is the second time \Nyou've faked your death.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.78,0:12:21.29,Main,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,They'll probably figure it out soon, \Nbut the situation's still chaotic.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.95,0:12:23.52,Main,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,They should consider
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.52,0:12:26.48,Main,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,your death sentence carried out for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.82,0:12:31.63,Main,Yuji,0,0,0,,Why would you go that far?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.97,0:12:34.91,Main,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,Because the people I cherish...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.38,0:12:37.58,Main,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,cherish you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.17,0:12:41.93,Main,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,I once shouldered
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.93,0:12:44.77,Main,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,a power greater than I could bear.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.77,0:12:48.16,Main,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,Though the power I thought \Nwas forced upon me
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.16,0:12:50.66,Main,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,turned out to be something \NI brought upon myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.66,0:12:51.97,Main,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,I'm not like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.36,0:12:55.18,Main,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,The power you shoulder isn't your own power.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.41,0:13:00.18,Main,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,You're not to blame.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.17,0:13:07.27,Main,Yuji,0,0,0,,You're wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.79,0:13:10.19,Main,Yuji,0,0,0,,It's not even a matter of blame.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.65,0:13:13.19,Main,Yuji,0,0,0,,I killed...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.33,0:13:13.40,Main,Fushiguro,0,0,0,,Itadori!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.50,0:13:19.67,Main,Yuji,0,0,0,,Fushiguro.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.92,0:13:20.24,Main,Fushiguro,0,0,0,,What are you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.18,0:13:22.86,Main,Fushiguro,0,0,0,,We're going back to Jujutsu High!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.35,0:13:25.88,Main,Fushiguro,0,0,0,,The barrier around Jujutsu \NHigh is weakened now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.88,0:13:28.05,Main,Fushiguro,0,0,0,,It's fine for you to return
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.05,0:13:29.94,Main,Fushiguro,0,0,0,,as long as no one sees your face directly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.51,0:13:33.04,Main,Fushiguro,0,0,0,,We'll meet up with the upperclassmen, then—
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.05,0:13:33.04,Main,Yuji,0,0,0,,Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.59,0:13:36.84,Main,Yuji,0,0,0,,Don't accept what happened like it's normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.90,0:13:39.80,Main,Yuji,0,0,0,,Don't negate what happened!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.71,0:13:44.60,Main,Yuji,0,0,0,,I killed people.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.24,0:13:49.06,Main,Yuji,0,0,0,,Because of me, so many people died!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.73,0:13:49.06,Main,Fushiguro,0,0,0,,Because of {\i1}us{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.87,0:13:53.31,Italics,Yuji,0,0,0,,Of course you'd say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.31,0:13:57.49,Main,Fushiguro,0,0,0,,Don't go giving up by yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.72,0:14:12.71,Main,Fushiguro,0,0,0,,We aren't heroes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.39,0:14:14.77,Main,Fushiguro,0,0,0,,We're jujutsu sorcerers.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.35,0:14:18.34,Main,Fushiguro,0,0,0,,There's no one who can \Njudge us in a true sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.33,0:14:20.59,Main,Fushiguro,0,0,0,,That's all the more reason
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.06,0:14:24.10,Main,Fushiguro,0,0,0,,we have to keep proving why we exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.97,0:14:27.00,Italics,Yuji,0,0,0,,You're wrong, Fushiguro.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.00,0:14:30.34,Main,Fushiguro,0,0,0,,We don't have time to worry \Nabout ourselves anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.96,0:14:31.97,Italics,Yuji,0,0,0,,{\an8}If you say that, you'll...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.93,0:14:33.22,Main,Fushiguro,0,0,0,,We have to keep saving people!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.22,0:14:34.72,Italics,Yuji,0,0,0,,...end up suffering...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.72,0:14:37.48,Main,Fushiguro,0,0,0,,I thought this was supposed to \Nbe your driving motive, anyway!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.96,0:14:39.01,Italics,Yuji,0,0,0,,{\an8}...the whole time you remain with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.01,0:14:40.23,Main,Fushiguro,0,0,0,,So start by saving me,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.89,0:14:42.44,Main,Fushiguro,0,0,0,,Itadori!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.97,0:14:45.99,Main,Yuji,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.47,0:14:48.57,Main,Fushiguro,0,0,0,,Noritoshi Kamo has set up
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.80,0:14:51.59,Main,Fushiguro,0,0,0,,a death game between those \Nhe granted cursed techniques.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.09,0:14:53.46,Main,Fushiguro,0,0,0,,The Culling Game.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.89,0:14:57.75,Main,Fushiguro,0,0,0,,Tsumiki has been drawn into this game, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.83,0:15:02.34,Main,Fushiguro,0,0,0,,Please, Itadori.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.42,0:15:10.30,Main,Fushiguro,0,0,0,,I need your power.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.97,0:15:22.56,Sign_Basic,ScreenRighttoLeft,0,0,0,,{\an3\fs14\fnTimes New Roman\b1\shad0\3c&HD69644&}The Culling Game <General Rules>\N{\fs10}1) After awakening their cursed technique,\Nplayers must go to a colony of their choice within 19 days\Nand pledge their participation in the culling game.\N 2) Players breaching the first rule shall be stripped of their technique.\N 3) Non-players shall become players upon entering a colony,\Nand their entry shall be taken as pledging to participate in the culling game.\N 4) Players will receive points upon ending the life of another player.\N 5) Points shall be designated based on the value that the game master gives their life, \Nand fundamentally a sorcerer will be worth 5 points\Nwhile non-sorcerers will be worth 1 point.\N 6) By spending 100 points,\Nnot counting the initial point value assigned to them, players may negotiate\Nwith the game master to add an additional rule to the culling game.\N 7) The game master must approve any additional rules\Nrequested under Rule 6 above, except when the Rule\Nwould significantly hinder the continuation of the culling game.\N 8) Players who do not show a change in points \Nwithin 19 days of joining or acquiring points\Nshall be stripped of their technique.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.56,0:15:22.98,Sign_Basic,ScreenFlash,0,0,0,,{\an8\fnTimes New Roman\b1\bord0\shad0\pos(320,5)}The Culling Game
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.98,0:15:23.36,Sign_Basic,ScreenFlash,0,0,0,,{\an8\fnTimes New Roman\b1\bord0\shad0\pos(320,5)}General Rules
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.56,0:15:23.94,Sign_Basic,ScreenFlash,0,0,0,,{\an8\fnTimes New Roman\b1\bord0\shad0\pos(310,5)}Within 19 Days
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.94,0:15:24.31,Sign_Basic,ScreenFlash,0,0,0,,{\an8\fnTimes New Roman\b1\bord0\shad0\pos(320,5)}Participate
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.27,0:15:25.57,Sign_Basic,ScreenFlash,0,0,0,,{\an8\fnTimes New Roman\b1\bord0\shad0\pos(320,5)}Breach
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.57,0:15:25.94,Sign_Basic,ScreenFlash,0,0,0,,{\an8\fnTimes New Roman\b1\bord0\shad0\pos(320,5)}Technique
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.94,0:15:26.23,Sign_Basic,ScreenFlash,0,0,0,,{\an8\fnTimes New Roman\b1\bord0\shad0\pos(320,5)}Stripped
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.94,0:15:27.36,Sign_Basic,ScreenFlash,0,0,0,,{\an8\fnTimes New Roman\b1\bord0\shad0\pos(320,5)}Entering a Colony
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.36,0:15:27.69,Sign_Basic,ScreenFlash,0,0,0,,{\an8\fnTimes New Roman\b1\bord0\shad0\pos(320,5)}Participate
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.90,0:15:29.32,Sign_Basic,ScreenFlash,0,0,0,,{\an8\fnTimes New Roman\b1\bord0\shad0\pos(320,5)}Ending
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.32,0:15:29.57,Sign_Basic,ScreenFlash,0,0,0,,{\an8\fnTimes New Roman\b1\bord0\shad0\pos(320,5)}the Life
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.53,0:15:31.11,Sign_Basic,ScreenFlash,0,0,0,,{\an8\fnTimes New Roman\b1\bord0\shad0\pos(320,5)}Sorcerer 5 Points
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.11,0:15:31.61,Sign_Basic,ScreenFlash,0,0,0,,{\an8\fnTimes New Roman\b1\bord0\shad0\pos(320,5)}Non-Sorcerer 1 Point
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.61,0:15:37.99,Sign_Basic,ScreenRighttoLeft,0,0,0,,{\an3\fs14\fnTimes New Roman\b1\shad0\3c&HD69644&}The Culling Game <General Rules>\N{\fs10}1) After awakening their cursed technique,\Nplayers must go to a colony of their choice within 19 days\Nand pledge their participation in the culling game.\N 2) Players breaching the first rule shall be stripped of their technique.\N 3) Non-players shall become players upon entering a colony,\Nand their entry shall be taken as pledging to participate in the culling game.\N 4) Players will receive points upon ending the life of another player.\N 5) Points shall be designated based on the value that the game master gives their life, \Nand fundamentally a sorcerer will be worth 5 points\Nwhile non-sorcerers will be worth 1 point.\N 6) By spending 100 points,\Nnot counting the initial point value assigned to them, players may negotiate\Nwith the game master to add an additional rule to the culling game.\N 7) The game master must approve any additional rules\Nrequested under Rule 6 above, except when the Rule\Nwould significantly hinder the continuation of the culling game.\N 8) Players who do not show a change in points \Nwithin 19 days of joining or acquiring points\Nshall be stripped of their technique.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.66,0:15:43.00,Show_Title,Screen,0,0,0,,{\fad(925,0)\shad1\be3\3c&H62BAB9&}JUJUTSU KAISEN
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.00,0:15:45.76,Flashback_Italics,Fushiguro,0,0,0,,Please, Itadori.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.27,0:15:48.35,Flashback_Italics,Fushiguro,0,0,0,,I need your power.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.22,0:15:51.60,Main,Yuji,0,0,0,,Okkotsu-senpai.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.43,0:15:54.79,Main,Yuji,0,0,0,,Sukuna is plotting something \Nthat uses Fushiguro.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.29,0:15:58.85,Main,Yuji,0,0,0,,He was probably able to take \Nover my body in Shibuya
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.85,0:16:02.29,Main,Yuji,0,0,0,,because I was force-fed ten fingers at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.29,0:16:05.26,Main,Yuji,0,0,0,,There are now 15 fingers inside me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.26,0:16:07.89,Main,Yuji,0,0,0,,Even if I'm fed the remaining \Nfive all at once,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.89,0:16:10.01,Main,Yuji,0,0,0,,I don't think he'll be able to take me over.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.01,0:16:11.27,Main,Yuji,0,0,0,,But even so,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.77,0:16:14.36,Main,Yuji,0,0,0,,if Sukuna does manage to take control again,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.36,0:16:15.84,Main,Yuji,0,0,0,,don't hesitate to kill me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.70,0:16:18.43,Main,Yuji,0,0,0,,I trust you can do that, Senpai.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.28,0:16:21.31,Main,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.20,0:16:24.04,Main,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,I'll do my best.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.86,0:16:25.97,Main,Yuji,0,0,0,,Fushiguro.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.46,0:16:27.90,Main,Yuji,0,0,0,,What do I need to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.85,0:16:30.79,Main,Fushiguro,0,0,0,,First, we return to Jujutsu High
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.79,0:16:33.00,Main,Fushiguro,0,0,0,,and contact Tengen-sama.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.77,0:16:37.93,Main,Fushiguro,0,0,0,,How can we release the \Nseal of the Prison Realm?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.72,0:16:41.24,Main,Fushiguro,0,0,0,,What is Noritoshi Kamo's actual goal,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.24,0:16:42.68,Main,Fushiguro,0,0,0,,and what moves will he make?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.17,0:16:45.96,Main,Fushiguro,0,0,0,,The culling game is an unprecedented \Nact of jujutsu terrorism,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.96,0:16:49.55,Main,Fushiguro,0,0,0,,and we need answers to those two \Nquestions to resolve the situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.00,0:16:53.43,Main,Fushiguro,0,0,0,,I think Tengen-sama's the only \None capable of answering them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.89,0:16:55.39,Main,Yuji,0,0,0,,What about that woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.39,0:16:57.30,Main,Yuji,0,0,0,,Wouldn't Tsukumo-san know?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.82,0:17:00.11,Main,Fushiguro,0,0,0,,I've already spoken with Tsukumo-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.11,0:17:01.82,Main,Fushiguro,0,0,0,,This was her plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.36,0:17:05.35,Main,Fushiguro,0,0,0,,She's also hiding away at Jujutsu High.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.62,0:17:08.04,Main,Yuji,0,0,0,,Hiding away?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.04,0:17:10.65,Main,Fushiguro,0,0,0,,Apparently, she doesn't want \Nto deal with the higher-ups.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.08,0:17:15.10,Main,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,The problem is Tengen-sama's \Nconcealment barriers.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.96,0:17:19.68,Main,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,Out of 1,000 constantly shuffling doors,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.68,0:17:23.99,Main,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,only one leads to the Tombs of the Star \Nwhere Tengen-sama resides.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.51,0:17:27.92,Main,Yuji,0,0,0,,So unless we can pick the right door,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.92,0:17:30.17,Main,Yuji,0,0,0,,we can't meet with Tengen-sama?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.46,0:17:35.80,Main,Yuji,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Fushiguro.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.23,0:17:46.83,Main,Yuji,0,0,0,,I'm going to ask now anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.83,0:17:52.69,Main,Yuji,0,0,0,,What happened to Kugisaki?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.76,0:18:00.99,Main,Yuji,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.50,0:18:05.53,Main,Yuji,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.81,0:18:15.08,Main,Yuji,0,0,0,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.48,0:18:18.65,Main,Choso,0,0,0,,We might be able to do something
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.91,0:18:21.18,Main,Choso,0,0,0,,about the concealment barriers.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.40,0:18:24.10,Main,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,You were listening?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.40,0:18:27.31,Main,Yuji,0,0,0,,What do you mean, Choso?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.04,0:18:29.85,Main,Choso,0,0,0,,You remember when Mahito stole
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.85,0:18:32.02,Main,Choso,0,0,0,,Sukuna's fingers and us \NDeath Paintings, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.20,0:18:35.52,Main,Choso,0,0,0,,We'll do the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.33,0:18:47.14,Main,Maki,0,0,0,,It's been... not that long, really.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.42,0:18:48.70,Main,Yuji,0,0,0,,Maki-senpai?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.89,0:18:50.90,Main,Yuji,0,0,0,,Oh, hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.64,0:18:52.92,Main,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,Maki-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.92,0:18:54.81,Main,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,Is safe for you to be up and moving already?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.81,0:18:56.75,Main,Maki,0,0,0,,Yeah, it's not an issue.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.14,0:18:59.26,Main,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,Not much I could do about the burns.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.26,0:19:01.95,Main,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,Scars remain, even with the \Nreverse cursed technique.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.95,0:19:05.72,Main,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,Though your Heavenly Pact of \Nphysical prowess is impressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.72,0:19:09.97,Main,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,At the very end, your life was saved by \Nthe strength of your body's endurance
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.97,0:19:12.13,Main,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,rather than your resistance to curses.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.36,0:19:14.60,Main,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,It's a shame the clan head didn't make it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.60,0:19:17.19,Main,Maki,0,0,0,,It's not like it was a competition.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.50,0:19:21.68,Main,Maki,0,0,0,,Megumi, how goes it with \NTengen-sama's barrier?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.38,0:19:23.56,Main,Fushiguro,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.97,0:19:25.25,Main,Choso,0,0,0,,I'll explain.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.96,0:19:28.34,Main,Choso,0,0,0,,On the way to the Tombs of the Star
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.34,0:19:32.42,Main,Choso,0,0,0,,is the forbidden vault holding Jujutsu High's \Ncursed tools and cursed objects, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.42,0:19:35.02,Main,Choso,0,0,0,,The remains of my brothers—
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.02,0:19:39.15,Main,Choso,0,0,0,,Noranso, Sho-oso, Tanso, \NSanso, Kotsuso, and Shoso—
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.15,0:19:41.41,Main,Choso,0,0,0,,are in the forbidden vault.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.41,0:19:43.77,Main,Choso,0,0,0,,Even if it's just their remains,\Nwith all six together,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.77,0:19:45.90,Main,Choso,0,0,0,,I should be able to sense their presence
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.90,0:19:48.18,Main,Choso,0,0,0,,using the side effect of my technique.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.78,0:19:50.03,Main,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,Good!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.03,0:19:51.53,Main,Maki,0,0,0,,That's great to hear,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.03,0:19:53.68,Main,Maki,0,0,0,,but who's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.25,0:19:58.73,Main,Yuji,0,0,0,,For now, you can say...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.44,0:20:01.50,Main,Yuji,0,0,0,,he's my older brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.93,0:20:05.02,Main,Choso,0,0,0,,Yuji!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.41,0:20:06.31,Main,Yuji,0,0,0,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.37,0:20:10.44,Main,Choso,0,0,0,,That one.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.38,0:20:12.91,Main,Choso,0,0,0,,I'm certain.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.91,0:20:15.60,Main,Choso,0,0,0,,My younger brothers are resting beyond here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.60,0:20:16.56,Main,Choso,0,0,0,,I'm opening it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.56,0:20:17.41,Main,Yuji,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.45,0:20:28.66,Main,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,Let's head down.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.13,0:20:33.54,Main,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,There's an elevator leading to \Nthe Tombs of the Star further in.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.08,0:20:36.29,Main,Yuji,0,0,0,,Choso.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.91,0:20:38.06,Main,Choso,0,0,0,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.00,0:20:40.91,Main,Choso,0,0,0,,I'll come back for you later.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.91,0:20:42.96,Main,Choso,0,0,0,,Please wait a little longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.71,0:20:50.01,Main,Yuji,0,0,0,,Blood stains?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.01,0:20:51.73,Main,Yuji,0,0,0,,Did something happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.73,0:20:54.22,Main,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,It was twelve years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.22,0:20:55.72,Main,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,Thinking back,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.72,0:20:59.62,Main,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,all of the distortions may \Nhave started back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.54,0:21:03.64,Main,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,All right, everyone, \Nthe main hall is up ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.26,0:21:21.49,Main,Yuji,0,0,0,,There's nothing here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.49,0:21:23.28,Main,Fushiguro,0,0,0,,This is the main hall?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.28,0:21:26.48,Main,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,No, he's rejecting us.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.05,0:21:29.80,Main,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,Tengen won't interfere with reality, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.80,0:21:32.70,Main,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,I thought it would be \Npossible to reach him now,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.70,0:21:34.64,Main,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,while the Six Eyes are sealed away,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.64,0:21:36.45,Main,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,but my prediction was naïve.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.26,0:21:43.21,Main,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,It's not all of us being \Nrejected... but just me?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.05,0:21:46.45,Main,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,Let's head back.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.45,0:21:48.35,Main,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,Tsumiki-san doesn't have time to spare.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.03,0:21:52.75,Main,Tengen,0,0,0,,You're leaving?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.08,0:21:55.43,Main,Tengen,0,0,0,,Nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.43,0:21:58.82,Main,Tengen,0,0,0,,Child of Zen'in, Descendant of Michizane,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.82,0:22:01.11,Main,Tengen,0,0,0,,Cursed Womb Death Painting,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.55,0:22:05.88,Main,Tengen,0,0,0,,and Vessel of Sukuna.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.28,0:23:42.70,Main,Tengen,0,0,0,,I must impose one condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.70,0:23:44.99,Main,Okkotsu,0,0,0,,We came here to learn how \Nto open the Prison Realm.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.17,0:23:46.47,Main,Tsukumo,0,0,0,,{\an8}No greeting for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.80,0:23:47.12,Main,Fushiguro,0,0,0,,Then why is this Culling Game...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.12,0:23:49.65,Main,Tengen,0,0,0,,...to force the evolution of mankind...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.88,0:23:51.66,Main,Shoko,0,0,0,,{\an8}...it's better for the rules if being \Nstripped means death, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.81,0:23:53.55,Main,Yuji,0,0,0,,If Sukuna does take control again,\Ndon't hesitate to kill me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.93,0:23:54.34,Main,Choso,0,0,0,,{\an8}Don't die out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.03,0:23:55.06,Next_Ep_Title,Screen,0,0,0,,Next Episode\N{\fs30}About the Culling Game

